caption: Great dining experience. Food was excellent overall. I had some minor nitpicks, but nothing I would truly consider negative. Dishes were, for the most part, not incredibly imaginative, but they were all executed very well with a general respect for the ingredients and seasonality. Wine pairings were all correct, though only one was truly remarkable. The outdoor lodge was an excellent compromise for socially distant dining. We had no problem with the size, but taller/ larger people may have trouble fitting inside.
I wasn't a big fan the first time I was there for dine-in two years ago, but totally fell in love with Bresca after I had it for takeout recently.

My friend and I came here for dinner this past Sunday in their Outdoor Lodge for their 4-course Prix Fixe dinner ($83 per person).  The lodges are super cute—great for pictures—they look like mini greenhouses and only fits up to two guests—they are individually heated too!  There is also a Bluetooth speaker if you want to set up and play your own music.  Food was delicious and well presented (in a fancy and bougie way).  We ordered the Coddle Egg, Foie Gras Gateau, Poached Lobster, Black Cod and the Iwate Wagyu Zabuton.  The wagyu was amazing, highly recommend this dish and worth the $15 upgrade charge!  I was not a huge fan of the Foie Gras, it tasted sweet and had the texture of a cake (not the typically Foie Gras taste I normally eat).  Desserts were great, we had the Ambrosia and Chocolate Crunch—they also brought out additional mini complementary desserts for us to try.  Also, we were able to order basic cocktails off the menu!  One thing I really appreciated about this place was that in between each course, they offered some suggested (complimentary) drink—either tea, broth, etc.—to cleanse your palette for the next course!  And service here is top notch!

outdoor sitting at noon was steaming hot and eye fiercingly bright but the foods were simply amazing. we added the aged duck to the course, it was expensive ($75 per person with full party participation needed) but was worth the try. Maybe I'd order it once in 3-4 times but would definitely on the first visit. I tried almost all menus on the course and none disappointed. would go for the lobster than the foie gras though. loved the wagyu too (+$)

BRESCA is my first Michelin restaurant. My sister and I wanted to live a little. Turns out, we lived A LOT! 🎉🎊 The 1.5 hour experience was actually almost 2 hours to enjoy a four course menu, cocktails, and all the surprises from the kitchen along the way (drinks and bites). Sherman helped us throughout to make good selections. The rest of the staff here pay attention to the details (almost mind readers). I took off my suit jacket and placed it on the bench; someone came to hang it up. I used my napkin to wipe a spill; someone brought me another one. New silverware with every plate. The chef actually served us the duck, which was another nice surprise. I haven't said much about the food - trust me, it was delicious.  Complex flavors. Stunning presentations. Perfect portions. Great memories. I smile even thinking about it. I encourage you to try a Michelin restaurant. I strongly encourage you to make this one your first one. Thank you all for your hard work 👍

Absolutely divine. We had the 4 course meal and asked the waiter for wine pairings which he did a fantastic job of choosing. The food was satisfying and unique. The cocktails were strong but perfectly balanced, would recommend “Bees Knees” and “Definitely for Rachel and not for Josh”. Will certainly be back to try more items on the menu, especially the duck and the “SK then scotch” cocktail.  I will say the mushroom that came with the Wagyu beef was extremely salty and I could not eat it, but that’s just my personal preference.
Delicious food, comfortable ambiance, great service
A bit overrated in my opinion, the dishes were good but not amazing. Service was great though! And loved the presentation

I spent roughly $500 on a valentines lunch. I didn’t haven any alcohol since I was doing dry February. Our lemonades equated to over $50. The food was overcomplicated, I don’t see how oranges compliment lobster. The wagyu beef tasted stringy and reminded me of a $10 silverside, poorly cooked. Our dinner went for 2 hours, not because the ambiance was so great we wanted to stay but the service was very slow. Will not be coming back. You expect to be amazed by the food when you’re paying big money. I would’ve still been disappointed if this was served by a 2 star restaurant.
Amazing!
Fantastic meal! The lodge prix fixe was a great menu, and the service was spectacular.
We had Incredible experience to beginning small drinks to walking out door with hot chocolate these folks crushed it!!

UPDATE:  We have been here 3 times since our first review. I took 2 stars away for lackluster communication and service tonight.  After being at our table for an hour exactly, I wasn’t allowed to order my husband another drink but no one really explained this; I had to figure it out. The waiter looked annoyed and didn’t explain a thing when I asked for the drink. He simply said “give me a second.” The next person (allegedly the manager) came by for our check. I told him I had asked the waiter for a drink for my husband and would need the bill adjusted. He then told me they were booked back to back and could not give us another drink but could recommend plenty of nice bars (during COVID in DC? Ok).  When he came back for signature I asked about the time limit. He said it was 1 hour 15 mins (this has never happened before and was not explained in the confirmation email). I told them two other tables were there before we came and are still enjoying drinks. I also told him we go there regularly and recommend the place to many, but were disappointed with this experience. He had zero explanation and simply apologized. The table of 4-6 continued to hang out and enjoy drinks.  They add automatic 22% tip which is usually  fine, but tonight that tip was not deserved. We were rushed while others got to stay much longer. We won’t be returning. Definitely not Michelin level tonight, Bresca.  ********  We went here based off of a friend's recommendation to do the Chef's Tasting experience. We were not disappointed. From the moment we walked in and got a delicious, refreshing welcome drink, to the last bite, everything was exceptional. I really enjoyed the 90s hip-hop instrumental music in the background; many may not notice it but we loved it and it took us back! Very pricey meal (with cocktails and a bottle of wine) but it was SO well worth the Michelin-star experience.
Fancy!

Celebrated by wife's birthday with their tasting menu in one of their outdoor dining bubbles. The experience was amazing! Felt very safe and comfortable in the bubble, with the heater. It was very tastefully done and just flowed so well with the restaurant. Very cool experience. The food and cocktails were delicious! Also the staff was friendly and not pretentious. Would give 6 stars if possible.
Exquisite duck. Must have. If there’s one thing they could improve - the decor (a bit mixed styles).

Hands down one of the best restaurants in DC. Much better food than Maydan or Rose’s Luxury, which also have a Michelin star. Remarkably, the restaurant has become even better during the pandemic. It’s the only one that has been able to make “to go” options just as good as their in person dining. The ambrosia dessert here is my favorite thing in the world. Although, heads up you must love tapioca.

Different Thanksgiving this year, of course, so I decided to order from Bresca even though it’s a 40 minute drive each way to pick up the meal.  It was totally worth it.  The food could not have been better.  Thoughtfully prepared, so it was easy to cook the turkey breast and leg and warm up the  delicious sides.  And the rolls rose and baked perfectly.  And the staff could not be lovelier. It was one of the best, if not the best, Thanksgivings I’ve ever had.  Looking forward to more “take-out” from Bresca.
One of the very best in town. Get the duck!
Absolutely phenomenal! We went there for our anniversary everything was perfect!

Superb food, unequaled service. The food was delectable and the staff went out of their way to make this a memorable experience. I highly recommend trying some of the cocktails and sitting by the bar if you want to watch the kitchen staff in action.

I have been to Bresca last weekend. I went for trhe prix fixe menu, and the whole experience was underwhelming. The poached beef, too salty; the ravioli was ok, but had a really mild teste; the fish was pretty average (and a really small portion), and the ganache was very sweet. It is really not worth the cost. I had good experiences with Bee at Home earlier in the year, but after last weekend, I wont be coming back.

I was excited when I saw that a Michelin Star restaurant was doing takeout, and Bresca did not disappoint! They put a lot of effort into packaging up complicated dishes, and the flavors were incredible.
Superb food, meticulously packed, well labeled, and easy to serve when you get home. On of the very best restaurants in DC. Easy and safe pickup for take out.

Decided to try Bresca to-go during restaurant week during covid and it definitely was the right choice! They seem to have worked the to-go method perfectly into their system. High quality food, Even at home. The menu listed it as portion for (4) which I didn't think it would feed 4 people for the price, however, I can't argue with the quality of the food! Will be trying it again!
Visited Jônt. See review there
Incredible!
Chef's Table Tasting Menu @ Jônt, upstairs in Bresca. Amazing experience, both for the eyes and the tastebuds.

We have ordered from Bresca now on three separate occasions in the past few months and each time the food is spectacular! Most recently, we ordered the special over Labor Day weekend and everything was delicious! We plan to continue to frequent this fine establishment.

I cannot believe this was my first time here! I absolutely LOVED this place. They took amazing COVID precautions and made it almost seem like we were not in a pandemic, like an escape from reality. Amazing service, Incredible food. Can I add more stars??!

I’m always impressed with BRESCA, but their pivot to take home options during COVID has been especially good. Over the past few months I’ve gotten to sample multiple parts of their new home menu and none have disappointed. Easy ordering online & in restaurant pick-up.
Been there twice. Both meals were excellent

Hand down absolutely amazing! We sat at the Chef’s table and the experience was one we will not forget. Being front and center smelling and watching each course being made seconds before it’s placed in front of you. Each dish was bursting with flavor. Can’t wait to go back!

The food is good but for the price and how noisy it is there are better options in the city.  Reviewing again from above post...the new chef's counter is awesome. Nice and intimate. Although music is loud in some spots.
Extremely delicious cocktails and food! I really wanna come back to taste other menu which I’ve not tried yet :)

We recently ordered online from Bresca for a special occasion meal. We were worried that the quality of the food would be compromised. We had eaten there once before and knew that the food is normally amazing. We were just so pleasantly surprised at how enjoyable the food delivered was. We tried 3 different menus between our 4-person family. All were absolutely delicious and arrived in time too not require heating even though we live 35 minutes away from Bresca. This is a restaurant absolutely worth preserving. We cannot wait to dine there in person again but for now we are just delighted to be able to enjoy it via delivery.
Bresca is incredible! Not only has it consistently been the best dining experience I’ve had in DC, but during COVID, their to-go dinners have also been amazing!

I love this place it’s in my top 5 of DC restaurants. The food is outstanding and the staff is always kind and attentive. I’ve ordered at least 4 times since the quarantine started and the quality is still the same. If you have the chance to get the duck dinner do it, it’s worth it. I can’t say enough good things about this place, give it a try, you won’t be disappointed.
Got takeout from Bresca. Even 30 min later the chicken was juicy and delicious. Also loved the charred avocado.

So good it brought tears to my wife's eyes. The bread was absolutely perfect. Crunchy but not too hard on the outside, the crust flakes as you bite into it and gives way to fluffy yet dense buttery inside. The wedge salad was well presented and tasted wonderful. The cocktail shrimp were large, delicious, and the cocktail sauce is on an entirely different level than any other you'll ever taste. The robuchon potatoes are what you have always wished mashed potatoes could be, taste and texture wise. The crispy baby potato on top was a pleasant touch. The mushrooms and shallots would shine by themselves in and other pairing but are proper supporting actors in this ensemble. They add but don't steal the spotlight from everything else. All you need to know about the steak is that it is textbook perfection. The chocolate tart mirrors the rest of the meal, in that it brings together every texture and flavor you expect but it adds something special in an exquisite yet understated presentation.
Outstanding service and food.   Wonderful flavors

Another great Micheline one-star restaurant in D.C.  Had the tasting menu with interesting flavor combinations in each dish.  Wine pairing wasn't that amazing.  Saturday night was also really loud and crowded.  You won't get in until after 9:30 if you don't have a reservation.   We'll go again on a week night and try the duck.  (We had a 6:15 reservation and it had already sold out.)
Gin World after party was amazing. Great cocktails and atmosphere!

Absolutely unbelievable restaurant! Worth the trip into the city and the price! The tasting menu with wine pairings was delicious! The flavors were so well thought through and complex. Awesome ambiance inside as well. Not too big. Will defiantly be back!

Went for Valentine's Day tasting menu. Overall decent (see Praises and Criticisms). A little too salty and rich overall.  Critiscisms -Boyfriend got the Senora G. It felt less  comforting and warm like the ingredients suggest and more like alcoholic tamarind flavored medicine (no warmth from chai or freshness from pear..?) -Tuna tartare was too salty for the size of the cracker sandwich. It could've played more in adding to the comforting grain tastes of the cracker. -Foie Gras with the fried waffle was too rich and heavy. Fried waffle felt soaked in oils -Rich foie gras was followed by a heavy tajarin with immense creamy buttery richness. (Too much) -Tajarin: lemon did not add enough freshness to offset richness, chicken skin could've been larger in pieces to add texture (muddled as crumbs) -Hokkaido scallops: these are notoriously sweet and fresh. The sauce and style masked any sweetness or freshness. If this was normal scallops, it would be fine but it doesn't use them well. The sauce is and crust make the whole thing very salty. More hazelnuts or use a nut with a less woody muted aftertaste like peanuts to add that punch (again buttery and salty after the last two was too much). -Beef tenderloin: the sauces felt disjointed and, again made the dish salty given the intense salty umami of the shiitake (which was great btw). Bordelaise was too much with all the sauces. -white chocolate tart: textures of tart filling and cream under the ice cream make the whole thing too soft. The cream below the ice cream had an odd bitter after taste like they used the leaves of a strawberry as well (not sure if intentional). The pastry shell was dense and stiff in an odd way that make the filling feel bland and dry.  Praise: -The palette cleanser was so tasty. I ordered another small glass. A person near me ordered a full cup of it! Mm. It was aromatic and fresh. It felt like lychee and guava candies making it homey for me. -my Sober Pineapple was delicious. The yeast after taste was really satisfying. Adding the basil gave a whole different experience. Freshness was helpful in eating the rich food (but I had to drink a lot of it) -initial tasting was really well thought out. Brioche crumb were aromatic. The crab gave in giving a very satisfying mouth feel. -cracker sandwich with tuna. Good spices, great cracker with aromatic flavors. -foie gras itself was delicious. Cocao nibs added such a well rounded dark note. -Shiitake mushroom and shallots were cooked amazingly well, added different depths to the tenderloin when eaten together with the creamy smooth white sauce. Bordelaise was well done. -pastry shell of tart had a great taste but odd mouth feel. The saltiness really added to the cream of the tart. (I just didn't like that filling overall).

The taste of their duck is really impressive and the beef rib was good too. If u want to try their duck I highly suggest u come before 6:00 clock since they only serve 4 duck per night and it run out quick.

I came here with my family while I was back in the DC area and was very impressed with what Bresca had to offer.  We made a 6pm reservation because it was either that or 8pm and I had read a few reviews that said that the duck gets sold out and I really really wanted to try it.  They have really interesting cocktails, so we started off the meal with a few of those and then also ordered a nice bottle of wine that was reasonably priced - only a 2x markup of a good bottle, so that was surprising.  For food, we shared: Bread and butter with trout roe - this was delicious, perfectly fluffy bread, butter that goes very well with the salt of the roe Shaved beef - this was interesting, but very good.  There were crispy pieces to it, and then shaved beef sprinkled around Beet salad - very nice flavors with a delicious sauces Scallop - also a solid dish Foie gras - as good as foie gras always is and this was well prepared.  The best part was the steamed brioche that you dip into the sauce of the foie gras after - it's like a dumpling almost Short Rib large format - wow this was incredible and a huge portion, definitely order if they have it on the menu Rohan Duck Presse - they only have 4 per night and we got one of them, and wow it was incredible.  They come and prepare table side so the presentation is fun too.  I order duck a lot and I'm struggling to think of one that I liked better than this.  The flavors are so amazing and condensed that there's a party in your mouth. The meat was cooked to a perfect medium rare, and all the accompaniments that come with the duck were great - the duck leg taste in particular was very good  For dessert, I got the foie gras cake pop, because I love foie gras.  It wasn't overpowering of foie gras, so you tasted more of the cake.  We also ordered the chocolate dessert from the tasting menu and a fruit meringue dessert I think.  The chocolate bar was quite delicious  They were very gluten free friendly for my husband, I think he could almost eat everything.  This place is definitely worth coming to!
Great French bistro
Good service, very salty food, definitely not a michelin star worthy. For the high prices, was very disappointed.
The pressed duck is totally worth getting there early! They only make a few a night. Excellent service, amazing food. Reasonable prices for a Michelin Star restaurant.
Beautiful place and good food
Went during restaurant week for dinner. The food was great, though very small portions which left me wanting more. But that was to be expected. I would want to come back to try their normal menu.
Excellent deal for restaurant week dinner at this 1-Michelin star restaurant. Our entire party was impressed with the food and service and had a great experience!

Like it, love it, gotta have it! This place is probably one of the better one star Michelin restaurants in the DMV area. The service, presentation, decor, and food all fit together like a Rolling Stones concert. I’m going to be back to try their limited duck breast!

We dined at Bresca during Restaurant Week January 2020.  The food is good however nothing spectacular.  We were rushed through our dinner service and given the check in under an hour without being asked if we wanted more wine or coffee.  Our waitress did an excellent job explaining the menu and wine pairings to the table next to us, however we didn’t receive the same level of service or explanations.  Maybe because it was Restaurant Week the staff wanted to get people in and out without providing the “excellent” service others mention in their reviews.  Bresca is worth a try IMO, however DC has many restaurants, both Michelin rated and not rated, that offer either better or just as good food and service.  I’ll get my Michelin star fix at Pineapples and Pearls, Blue Duck Tavern, Rose’s Luxury... next time.

We went for restaurant week. Everything was exquisite! I want to come back another time but they have just 2 vegetarian options on the menu and neither are main dishes. If they had more options for vegetarians, it would be 5 stars.

Always have a great time at BRESCA great food, great atmosphere and the staff are always friendly, on my last visit was served by Luca. Add this to your places to visit in Washington you wont be disappointing.

Bresca was a fantastic experience. The decor was great, staff were friendly and knowledgeable, cocktails were delicious, and the food impeccable.  Having now been a few times, I can confidently say that Bresca is one of my favorite meals in the city. If you are lucky enough to arrive when they still have the duck in stock, I highly recommend it. The pierogis are also top class.

I surprised my husband with a birthday dinner here. In making reservations, I opted for a 5:15 pm reservation knowing they had limited duck availability each night.  The interior is so whimsical and quirky, with its honeycomb accents and live moss wall. Upon sitting down, I ordered the Bee's Knees ($16). I was pleasantly surprised to see that it came out of a bee-shaped cocktail glass, after having read on Yelp that they had discontinued its use after several of these gorgeous glasses breaking in the past. The drink itself was lovely and balanced with gin, mead, honey, and lemon.  The food menu was divided into snacks, medium plates, and large plates. The server recommended that if we order a large plate, we could order 1-2 medium plates and that would suffice. After a couple of perusals and questions to our server, we ultimately settled for the following plates:  + Broccoli pierogi ($23): smoked cipollini, goat gouda, potato, and onion soubise + Scallop mi-cuit ($16): turnip, buttermilk, horseradish, lime + Rohan duck à la presse ($118): 21-day dry-aged duck breast with coriander and pink peppercorn crust and local honey; savory duck leg tart with mountain rose, mustard seed, and bronze fennel; and a salad of braised apple, baby fennel, noisette butter, and mustards  The pierogi was spectacular. I wish there were more. They should make it as a large plate. The pièce de résistance was definitely the duck. This is an old-school French dish, where a traditional press for this technique extracts the blood and bone marrow from the duck into a sauce. The juices are collected in a pan and strained, and the sauce is served on top of the duck. There are only four ducks available each night, served first come, first served. The best part of the whole experience is that the pressing of the duck and the cooking of the sauce are all done right next to you at the table! The duck was fantastic. The sauce. Oh, the sauce. That was extraordinary. A magical, sublime moment.  We had a wonderful dinner. The food, the service, the ambiance were all remarkable. Very worthy of its accolades and the price tag.
Amazing food! Pretty flexible kitchen with our dietary restrictions and the server was very helpful in helping us choose food and drinks.
It is so good.  We came to visit my son and daughter in law.   They suggested this great restaurant.  The food was exquisite.   The best ever.   Will come back in the future.

This place was beyond incredible. The food was out of this world delicious and fun. The service was outstanding and the servers were passionate about the dishes (and very well trained). The cocktails are equally as unique and refined. I would give them 10 stars if I could! [Instagram @sipsavorslay]
Outside unassuming... inside, great atmosphere, food was an experience in flavors... well deserving of that Michelin rating... highly recommend
The duck is *insane*... It's expensive ($120 at the time), but it is worth every single dollar. The breast meat was perfectly cooked and the rouennaise sauce was amazing.

Great service, excellent food. We arrived early enough to try the duck and it was delicious. The atmosphere was fairly casual, not stuffy at all. Fairly affordable for a Michelin started restaurant, yet I feel we more than got our money’s worth. Will definitely be back!

Bresca is a fantastic experience with great food, drinks, and service. The menu is exceptional and every time we go they have something new. Some of the dishes are incredibly memorable (the pressed duck comes to mind). While it is relatively pricey, I would call it very good value compared to other restaurants that serve food of this quality.
Went here with friends who were in town to visit. It was a fun experience!
They charge high price but deliver excellent food!!!Great services!!!
Creative food presented beautifully. The service is exceptional, attentive but unobtrusive. Thanks to our wonderful server, who was so patient.
The food here is just so good... and the service is just impeccable.
One of the more affordable Michelin starred restaurants in the DC area, but still the excellent quality you would expect. Get reservations ahead of time though.

I was prepared to be disappointed, as we arrived slightly early for our reservation (10 mins) and were kindly told we could visit a neighboring bar or stand near the door while we waited. There was literally no where to stand other than pressed against the wall near the door. Not an inspiring start.  From there on, the experience was only positive as we were sat on time and treated with excellent beverages, perfectly thought out appetizers (the shaved beef is a novel concept that was almost as good as the brioche), and an amazing take on roast chicken.  The menu is quite limited, but that obviously allows them to focus on the few dishes they have to achieve borderline perfection. Worthy of its single Michelin star and recommended.
Small portions, high prices, excellent food and service. Exactly what I was expecting!

I love this place. Everyone I encountered was so nice and so helpful. It was my birthday dinner so my party got the tasting menu. It was definitely worth it. Every item that came out was so complex with flavor and very good.
Three things to know:  1) I will put their cocktail list against anyone in the world. 2)welcome to flavortown 3)my girl Jess behind the bar runs sh$@. Props to the queen.  Holla!!  M

While this is fine dining, it does not have a formal feel, if anything it has a trendy casual vibe.  The meal itself was a fine dining experience.  I had the lamb saddle which had a crispy, smoky texture with perfectly cooked lamb and lamb short rib.  The staff were very informal but quite knowledgeable on the menu and wine pairings.  I had a luscious Syrah which the server recommended.  To start the meal I had the honey infused gin cocktail which reminded me of a juice pack, but enjoyable.  This was an excellent meal and service so I give them 5 stars.

Tasting menu was delicious and service excellent. Kitchen and servers accommodated unusual food allergy with grace and professionalism. Constructive feedback… Management needs to take necessary steps to improve noise level and atmosphere. More comfortable chairs and warmer lighting would help.

We came to Bresca for dinner after hearing nothing but good things. We did the tasting menu with wine pairing (the whole table must participate) along with the bread and butter and a cocktail to start.  I was really impressed by the interior design at Bresca and the attention to detail each course delivered. I was especially happy with the pasta they offered, and everything paired really well with the wines. I also really enjoyed the Wagyu flat iron along with the Fois Gras cake pops. There was a point in the evening where they served the wine a little bit too pre maturely before the next course but that’s hardly an issue.  Overall a really great experience, and I look forward to dining here again.
Definitely worth the hype. The food was amazing, the cocktails were interesting, the service impeccable, and the aesthetic was fun. Good for a date or fun with friends. 5 stars all around.
Great atmosphere, even better service, and a wholely innovative menu! We had a great experience with the Prefix menu, while sitting at the bar.
Bold, creative and rare creations.
We at e the tasting menu and it was extremely good. Only minus is bad acoustics (lot of noice).
Exceptional in every way. Food, service and dining experience. Thank you so much for making our anniversary special. Jessie did a wonderful job along with the rest of the staff.
Those were some amazing flavors and presentations.

Two stars because this is a Michelin rated restaurant. 1. Cocktails are too sweet, a good cocktail should be well balanced. I have eaten all over and when comparing this to Alinea in Chicago or other Michelin rated restaurants it's is a let down.  2. The chefs tasting menu comes out far too slowly. You shouldn't have people falling asleep at their tables waiting for the next course as I saw tables near me nodding off or taking bathroom breaks to kill the time.  3. The palette cleanser was a shot of vinegar. Why did you think this was a good idea.  4. Vinegar was an overall theme here from start to finish, coming back in many dishes, where it certainly didn't need to make an appearance was in the strange, highly salty chocolate cake that that pickeled cherries.  To top it all off we finished with a press post of coffee that came 1. Boiling hot (not recommended for best coffee, 176 to 190 is just fine. 2. The coffee itself was an aggressive  roast.  Other items, your Wagyu should be medium rare which is awesome and how I recieved it, but make your plate hot, because by the time the meat made it to my table it was lukewarm. It should still be hot to my tongue.  Wait staff was nice and the restaurant was pleasant, but how you outrated the Blue Duck astounds me.
Amazing spot. Unique and high-end cocktails with dope food.
Perfect in every aspect
Came to celebrate my birthday and was not disappointed. The food was creative and delicious and the wine pairings really elevated the whole experience.

Literally the best meal I have EVER had! Went about a week and a half ago after learning of an old friend’s connection to the place. Dined with my partner. We were both impressed with the decor upon entering, as a bartender, we sidled up to the bar. The thematic consistency in menus, decor and accoutrements did not go unnoticed. We decided on the tomato habanero cocktail and the Bee’s Knees (which absolutely lives up to it’s name. Where can I get those glasses?), And ordered the scallop small plate, as a starter, followed by the dry aged strip loin, cooked medium rare. I could go on for hours describing the wonderful food, but I will not, I’ll use one word, Succulent!  We will be back, and we won’t be alone, gotta share the wealth.  Thank you.  Our staff, that was superb, were Nico and Nick, behind the bar.

My boyfriend and I dined at Bresca during restaurant week and the food was truly disappointing. It was packed with upscale and unique ingredients and still managed to taste like absolutely nothing. Our meal was sort of like the noise cancelling headphones of food - all the components cancelled each other out. Its honestly impressive that the chef managed to make foie gras - one of the most famously flavorful ingredients - taste like cardboard. I would have preferred a frozen chicken dinner from the Trader Joe's next door. I will not be going back to Bresca ever, even though I live just blocks away.
Great food, service and atmosphere.
(Translated by Google) Great food so definitely a place to visit!  (Original) God mat så absolutt et sted du må besøke!
Definitely worth the hype. The food was amazing, the cocktails were interesting, the service impeccable, and the aesthetic was fun. Good for a date or fun with friends. 5 stars all around.
Aug 2019 restaurant week menu was underwhelming. Monk fish was bland and undercooked and barely warm. Service and apple based cocktail were good. Overall disappointed.
Quite possibly the best dining experience I've ever had.
Top notch food excellent service.
The food was delicious! We loved the meat and the dessert with passion fruit

Outstanding on every level.  Beautiful space, spot-on service, creative craft cocktails, and oh the food.  Some friends and I enjoyed Bresca last January 2018, and just had to return last week when I was back in DC.  They've since earned a Michelin star, and I must say it was well deserved!
One of the very best restaurants in DC. The attention to detail is spectacular. We got the tasting menu which was 5 courses for $65. Definitely worth it. The drinks are amazing as well.
Great food and atmosphere. Highly recommend the tasting menu. Staff are amazing.

So I know this place has one star already, so it is not new but let me tell you it is still under the radar for what it is... the tasting menu is only $65 a person for 5 (ends up being 7 counting small bites and it’s arrangement) courses. It is greatly worth it to have the tasting menu as the plates are well thought out and not one plate did not have the correct combination of flavors well thought out and tested to a T. They are a sustainable restaurant using every part of every ingredient and treat it in such a way that you can feel the love and enthusiasm that the kitchen puts into it. The waitress was extremely kind and when we waited a bit longer for one of the courses she didn’t think twice to top up our paired wines. This place will most likely get its second star, so take advantage of this opportunity to frequent this if you are local or try it while traveling, as that tasting menu should be up in the $85-95 range and is greatly worth it. Ps. Not all pictures posted as I was too excited when a couple dishes came out.

Shared the sourdough appetizer, the halibut and the chicken.  Everything was delicious.  For cocktails we tried the big in japan and the bee's knees which were both great. Service was good and our table overlooked the sidewalk, great for people watching.

Food was very good, the portions were just. The shaved beef was great, The foi gra (however your spell it) with the sufganiot was amazing And so does the rest of the dishes we had. Service was a delight, only it was very hard to hear our server as the overall ambience of the place is noisy. Price wise the place did not completely deliver, I'd expect that at these price points we'll get better attention to details.  Bottom line : Completely ok.

Went for late dinner. I have dined at most of the Michelin starred restaurants and felt some were over rated. Not bresca. It has an interesting mix of drinks. Service is excellent. A small but good selection of wines. The experience is suppose to be one of sharing plates. We ordered the sourdough served with farmers cheese. It was a great start. Then came the asparagus salad. The asparagus was perfect.  The halibut was also perfect with a nice mix of veggies and a sauce that was the perfect accent. The tenderloin was cooked perfect served with a nice salad. The sauce for the beef was amazing. I would buy it and use it every day if possible. Dessert was an ambrosia which had great flavor and highly recommend. I did not think I would like it. We also tried the four grass pop and it was okay and the only thing we had that did not wow us. Overall I would give them 2 stars and highly recommend.
The duck is divine.
Had a wonderful dinner tonight with friends. Wishing chef Ryan and the Bresca crew chief continued success.

This restaurant is consistently amazing. From food to service to the beverage program Bresca delivers time and time again. Chefs plates and creations are incredibly well thought out and excited. Wine list is not huge but it's expertly curated to pair with the food. The beverage program compliments everything in such a delightful way. Just as expertly as the food is crafted so are the cocktails. I can't say enough food things about this place. If you're feeling fancy try the duck press!

It's definitely the best Michelin star restaurant I've been to in DC. Start to finish, the experience got better with every second. The appetizer good. They may have been the only let down. The entree was awesome. We got the young chosen. It was delicious. The chicken breasts were baked perfectly with with percent crisp skin. There was a brioche and herb panade filling between the skin and the meat. It was just perfect. It came with veggies and what tasted like a tamarind sauce. The legs were deep fried and sweetened. It was just offer. It came with a dip and the dip was perfect. For dessert, I ordered tropical ambrosia. The tropical fruit in the outside felt weird in the beginning. But once I mixed everything together, it was heaven. It was definitely worth the money and I would highly recommend it.
Top restaurant in DC!

Fantastic Michelin star restaurant with interesting decor with a live wall and honey/honeycomb theme and a nice bar. A more casual setting, but terrific service nonetheless. Great craft cocktails here although they do have wine and beer as well. The menu is such that you can either graze through an array of small plates or go with the standard appetizer then entree format. We especially enjoyed the foie gras pate with hot beignets which was genius as the paste melts onto the hot bread... The desserts were also very interesting and delicious. On street parking only and in an interesting neighborhood. With a trip!

WOW. This was absolutely incredible. Came in unexpectedly and my date and I both had the tasting menu. I’m gluten intolerant and they adapted flawlessly. The snacks were puffed beef tendon and asparagus, both were delicious. The next course was a masterpiece, scallops in a lime buttermilk sauce with caviar, grapes, and snap peas. This was a very well done play on sweet and salty, and several textures. When you got that perfect bite with each piece it was HEAVENLY. They next course was ricotta gnudi, which my date said was splendid, but as I’m GF they provided my an asparagus dish over potatoes that was very good. The main course, veal with veggies and a mushroom puuree was phenomenal. The flavor was wonderful, the veal could’ve even been cut with a fork it was so tender and juicy. The desert was a Black Forest desert with cherry sorbet, which tasted purely of black cherries (in the absolute best way possible). My replacement was a mango dragonfruit dish with very light, crisp, well cooked meringue that was another masterpiece of making the perfect bites. The plates were well balanced, packed with rich, delicate, enticing flavors, and more than worth the trip. This was wonderful.

This was hands down the best meal I’ve had in DC. The duck is king here, if you dine here and don’t get the duck - honestly I’m sorry for you.* Every dish we had was something about which to write home. Foie gras and beignets was not something I ever expected to need in my life, but it was so exciting and so good. Just inject it into my veins. Did I mention it was so good?  Service was obviously great. The cocktails were all great, but the Bees Knees comes in a cool bee cup - so definitely go with that one. The design of the restaurant was so cool; it was a great atmosphere. Honestly, the bathroom was so nice that I could have eaten my whole meal in there and been happy.  If I had to come up with a complaint, it would be that I would have liked some music. We ate there on a Tuesday though - perhaps they have music on weekends.  You should probably just go make a reservation now.  *Unless you’re a vegetarian. We did have two vegetarians with us and they both loved the meal despite being sadly deprived of the duck.

Best dining experience I’ve had in a long time! Restaurant was able to protect our reservation after running late and were so accommodating and understanding. Shout out to Sue for amazing service throughout our whole meal. Food was outstanding. I highly recommend the foi gras beignets.

(Translated by Google) We tried the menu. The best scallops. The Bride Mantel cocktail was delicious. Very original. Very good service I missed a tablecloth on the table. It must improve some details. The appetizer I did not like much, they were pork rinds (?) And one asparagus with white pork bacon. If it had been an Iberian bacon, it would have been up to par. For a Spanish a pork crust at a Michelin star restaurant is a bit disappointing. The decoration of the place did not seem to me anything of the other world.  (Original) Probamos el menú. Lo mejor los scallops. El cocktail Bride Mantel estaba delicioso. Muy original. El servicio muy bueno. Eché de menos un mantel sobre la mesa. Debe mejorar algunos detalles. El aperitivo no me gustó mucho, eran cortezas de cerdo (?) y uno espárragos con tocino de cerdo blanco. Si hubiera sido tocino de ibérico hubiera podido estar a la altura. Para una española una corteza de cerdo en un restaurante de una estrella Michelin es un poco decepcionante. La decoración del local no me pareció nada del otro mundo.
The food and service was unbelievable. It takes a lot to create to craft an experience like that! Well done! I highly recommend it to anyone.

Beautiful open space, great cocktails, and the food is outrageous. The drinks came out immediately, and the food followed soon after. The service is excellent and the kitchen/bar are both on the ball. Excellent.
Phenomenal.
Nice food. Bad accoustics spoiles the dinner Approach of staff not interested and arrogant
Choreography of the floor is well paced, although slightly a half beat ahead. The signature duck is too much food for two. It could be split for two or four.
Super inventive menu.  Amazing drinks.

What a lovely dining experience. On an otherwise unassuming block of 14th Street, BRESCA was quite a delight. Service was impeccable, the interior of the space was modern but approachable. The food was beyond. The dishes were so unique and tasty, I could’ve tried one of everything and been content. Drinks were unique and worth the price. I would highly recommend BRESCA and will be returning.

Delicious selection of small plates. Definitely go with a few people so you can try everything. The sweet bug mug doesn’t come with every drink 😒 but it’s a nice novelty. Worth the price of admission to try it once and get some new flavors in you. Not dying to return tho.
The atmosphere is very warming and the food amazing .
World class dining in DC. Get the Foi and the Duck if you can .

Our experience with Bresca's March 2019 tasting menu ranged from mediocre to brilliant. The bold and tasty palette cleansing was apple cider shrub was followed by a flavourless oyster and disappointing beef tendon puff. Fortunately, the dishes mostly improved from there. The Shima aji was well balanced and the smoked potato perogies were sumptuous. The guinea hen was well cooked and presented in two ways but the taste was nothing special. Finally, dessert was good, but unidimensional. Of note, the main dining room is ludicrously loud at full service.
Great food, drinks, and staff!

Bresca is cute and cozy but modern and sophisticated at the same time. It's a must-try on the DC high-end list. Love all of the craft cocktails, and the dish presentation is beautiful and artistic. Several delicious vegetarian options as well. Wonderful service with truly attentive staff.
Double thumbs down. Poor acoustics, snarky waitress, left hungry.

Excellence is a standard adhered to at this restaurant in both food and service. The menu is fresh and unique, well prepared and delicious. The service is great, every server is focused on making your visit special. As a party of 4 we chose the tasting menu with wine pairing, Each course was superb, the quail was prepared two ways with a rich flavorful sauce, the wines we thoughtfully selected, very good. A fun, lively restaurant with great food and amazing service, a wonderful experience.

I visited Bresca for the first time tonight and will most definitely be returning.   The duck was delicious, the cocktails were perfect, and the service was impeccable.   You must try the Perrogi and the pasta dish they serve!!

Whether the cocktails or the food, Bresca offers delicious menu items. My husband and I ordered from the sample menu. If 1 person gets the sample menu, then everyone at the table also has to participate. I don't usually like wines or alcohol, but I was impressed with their paired sparkling wine and cocktails. The staff was amazing and smartly made suggestions for food or drinks based on my requests. The savory vegetables and sauces complemented the variety of tuna, red snapper, and wagyu beef. It was also my first time trying sea urchin, but I was very pleased with its smooth creamy texture.  Each dish from sample appetizer all the way through to dessert were delicious. And while my husband and I dressed formally, Bresca has a more casual atmosphere that allows smart casual and business casual clothes.
Delicious from start to finish. Outstanding service and knowledge of the menu for both cocktails and meal.
Amaze!!

Absolutely amazing meal with amazing service. Every part of the meal was a great experience. From being sat down at our table and greeted in a professional manner. Without even saying anything the staff knew when something had to be done at our table and just stepped right in.  The atmosphere was fairly loud, but it quieted down when it was later in the night. Every single dish was fantastic, the highlight being the Earl Grey dessert. This place is definitely deserving of it's Michelin star. Overall a great experience.
Made a reservation for a special dinner, and they called to cancel because they will be “closed for unforeseen circumstances” ...hope I can make a nice reservation last minute, thanks!!!
Had an amazing experience. Try the duck press!

Well prepared, Instagram friendly food. The staff are professional and charming, and the clientele are all well groomed and make for good people watching. An interesting range of wines. There are some feature family serving mains that are eye poppingly expensive, but this is not an area of DC for the financially faint of heart
Fabulous food. Amazing attention to flavors.
Went for my birthday dinner in October 2018. Concept is pretty similar to tail up goat but everything was top notch- food, service, ambience.
Not good.

I rarely leave a restaurant impressed, but Bresca left a great impression. Service is superb, decor is chic. I didn't have a cocktail, but they had a nice wine selection. The food was excellent, I can't wait to return!

Wonderful and knowledgeable wait staff who are well versed on the menu. Food was refreshing and flavourful. Highly recommend the Mackerel, wonderfully fresh and diverse flavors. My favorite dish by far. The waffles were a little heavy on the oil but the foie gras was delicious. Wonderful flavors in every dish, no complaints.

One of my favorite spots on 14th street. Great retro modern design, pleasant and professional service, inventive cocktails and of course solid French-accented food. Quality is high and consistent based on multiple visits. I hope they stay in that space and thrive.
The rabbit and beef were both excellent. The service, however, was a little lacking. It took 45 minutes for our drinks to be served.
Very good food.  Portions are very small and it is expensive but everything is very tasty and a lot of unique dishes.  Service also very good for Dc. Excellent wine

New hype in town, but merely above average. The cocktails came in fun glassware, but did not go beyond that. The food is tasty, but not amazing... for the price. Beware, portions are small, so prepare yourself to get several dishes to leave satiated, which will leave your wallet more on the empty side.
One of our favorite meals in DC. Great for a birthday!

Very displeased with the experience. They ran out of 3 major dishes at 9 pm on a Saturday. Be aware, it is very loud inside the restaurant. We could barely hear or understand our server Maurice.  Get the pierogi and the dairy cow.
Elegant setting with amazing foods. Highly recommend for a dating site or just a small gathering.

The food was just ok for a 2 michelin star restaurant..!! The dishes were like a hit or miss..some were good some were just meh.. Guess Michelin stars dont matter much.. but it was nice this place had an a la carte menu rather than a set price set course Dinner menu... gives access to all people for a fine dining experience.. the Staff were really nice too.. I d give it a 5 star if the Food had wowed me.. It didn't.. So taking away the 2 stars the michelin weirdos gave out...
One of the best meals all year! Super fun cocktails too!
Love it!

The atmosphere here is extremely inviting and definitely for all types of guests. Flavors and variety of dishes were absolutely amazing and the cocktails and wine are extremely complementary to all that they’re accomplishing here.
Incredible. Everything is delicious, the duck especially
The food was excellent for a wide variety of tastes and the atmosphere was relaxing and inviting.  A great neighborhood bistro.

Oh Bresca, if I lived in Washington, I would come by the restaurant weekly (but monthly for practicality). We had the fois gras and waffles. The toffee and banana helped with the saltiness of the fois gras. The cute duck feet plate for the waffles was such a cute touch. The scallops dish was just amazing. It wasn't just the scallops that shined, the catelinni, the different purees and the pickled onions tasted great and harmonized well together. The passionfruit dessert was larger than I expected and great for sharing. At first I thought it was just a meringue on top but to my surprise there was more depth in this dessert. I left the restaurant full but wanting to try more dishes. I would definitely recommend this place!
Beets and the swordfish were awesome, the large plate beef and the small plate broccoli not so much.  Server was great but service was super slow.
Unique, innovative and incredibly delicious dishes for sharing, a great wine selection, and impeccable service in a lively restaurant with an energetic vibe inside. Loved it, and we'll be back!
Small plates are more appetizer-sized and mains can feed 2-4. Everything was amazing including cocktails.

Everything about our experience at Bresca was amazing. Every single dish that was brought out to the table was absurdly delicious. The staff was very nice, accommodating, and able to provide helpful recommendations on beverages and food. They will probably have a Michelin star by next year based on the quality, variety, and ingredients in their plates. We're going to go back as much as possible.
Delicious, inventive food and great service.
Visited here before they got their *. Dont go unless you have time to enjoy their pace. Food is great. Service is great. Deserved the *.
Great lamb.

A great place to eat in DC. The cocktails are really good, and very unusual. Our server did a great job at giving us recommendations about food and by choosing our second round of cocktails. On the other hand, the food was amazing, it’s a very small menu, but it means that they do the food right. We ordered way too much food, had some left overs, but it was completely worth it. Definitely visiting again!
Excellent. Great food, great service.  The servers are very knowledgeable about all of our questions. Not cheap, worth it if you can afford it.  Definitely going back.
Lamb BBQ dish is one of the best dishes in D.C! Great service too.
I have had 4 meals here and I am yet to have a mediocre bite! Excellent spot.
The environment was pleasant, the staff was friendly, and all of the food was delicious! Worth the money .
Amazing food, love the atmosphere
Tasty
Excellent food and service. Allocate plenty of time as they want you to enjoy the experience.

We were introduced top this place through the Dine & Dash charity event.  it was awesome,  the vibe, drinks and small bites were amazing. The ambrosia dessert (pictured),  I hope they have it on the regular menu.  definitely going back!! A must try and service was excellent as well.

Good service. Food was pricey, but not bad when you go with a group. Unfortunately didn't get a picture of the steak BUT OMFG you gotta get it. It's pricey, sure, but every piece melts in your mouth. Really good food. Fun atomsphere but would NOT RECOMMEND IF YOU ARE AFRAID OF BEES since the whole place is bee themed! even the bathroom.

No two walls are the same in this hip space. An accent wall off moss and succulents fortells the intricacy of the dished to be served. Lamb lovingly cooked over 48 hours, tartare tarts if umami delight  and foie gras crafted with citrus and bright berries.  This fascinating space hold the pearl of the 14th street dining scene. Seeking a fine meal served in a conversational space, Bresca does not disappoint!

Bresca will make you melt with happiness and satisfaction. Off the charts food, unique and cool vibes, knowledgeable and accommodating staff. Perfect evening out in DC!  P.S. Still dreaming about the desserts!
Bangin!
Exquisite food but small menu. Friendly staff and expensive

We visited Bresca on a quiet, snowy, Tuesday evening. Our server was excellent. They were extremely knowledgeable about the food and the menu. The server made us feel welcome and was passionate about the food. It was one of the most unique dining experiences I’ve had in DC. Each dish has an exciting presentation. Everything we tasted was full of harmonized flavors. This a truly a gem on 14th street.

The good news is the food is terrific.  Not a single dish we ordered was less than excellent.  The bad news is that the restaurant is so loud that it felt assaultive.  It was not possible to have a conversation.  The noise kind of hit us as we entered but I thought I would get used to it.  In retrospect I am sorry we did not leave immediately.  I ended up with a headache and half an hour after we left, my head is still reeling from the assault.  We would have liked to have had dessert but we both could not wait to get out of there.  It was a miserable experience despite the excellent food.  We will not be back.

Went here for post dinner dessert and drinks and this place is amazing! It used to be the first floor of Policy. The drinks we had were absolutely delicious and the dessert was so cool. It was the strawberries and cream. It was a devine experience. The nitro cake batter definitely added some theatrics to it, but the cake lived up to the hype.

As a hater of French food I would have never come here unless begrudgingly dragged (drug? Sorry grew up small town) and treated to food. I also don’t like cocktails or trying new things. This place laughs at my ignorance and gently lets me know my pallet has much more to explore and enjoy. Recommend seeing Kristin as she will take care of you and make you feel welcome.

Top notch restaurant.  We started the night by ordering drinks that were truly whimsical and the night only got better.  Every dish we tried on the menu was amazing from the crudo, burrata salad, 62 degree egg and the steak dinner and dry aged squab.  I typically dislike beef and almost always avoid ordering it, but they have turned into a dish that has you craving for more.

Excellent food. Great dishes for sharing. Cocktails are creative both in terms of taste and presentation. Very friendly staff. They helped me order something online that I really liked in the restaurant.

absolutely loved the intimate setting, the creative cocktails and the service was great as well! The food was very adventurous and full of delicious flavors - we were especially blown away by the steak special!
Amazing French fare with a Catalan name.  Get the short rib.
It's good. Eat here if you have an opportunity.
Perfect all around. Great food (everything was exceptional), great service, great drinks, great ambience.
weird looking food but taste ok
Great food great service !!!
In times where there are too many good restaurants, Bresca (which translates from Catalan into honeycomb) breaks the mold with an innovative menu setup, great quality and fun options.
Great experience! We had to wait a bit for our table but they more than made up for it with excelent food and service!

What a wonderfully refreshing addition to the DC food scene! Bresca is peerless among restaurants on the 14th St Corridor. Despite the Catalan name, the menu is surprisingly Scandinavian in style. And what perfectly executed dishes. The complimentary cocktail at the beginning of the meal was a lovely touch, and the bar was accommodating enough to make a delicious non-alcoholic version for those who chose to forego. The pastrami beets turned out to be akin to Danish smørrebrød, it’s slightly dried bread a perfect base for creamy spiced beets and smoky cheese. The star of the meal was the char, beautifully plated and complex, with new potatoes and tangy lemon.  I will go back, and often.
By far the best of service anywhere. The variety of flavor was over the top! Many thanks for new treats on 14th .
Every course was delicious. Pricey but worth it.
Food and drinks were very good. Had to wait about 25 minutes even with a reservation though.

Small plates,  expensive,  but innovative. The menu is seasonal, but when I was there,  the PB&J pate was excellent, but honestly,  everything was fresh,  well prepared and executed.  More of a foodies place rather than somewhere for comfort food.
Awesome restaurant: food, service, drinks,decor and for dc, even the prices are good
Altogether a very nice meal, staff was knowledgeable and helpful. Can't recommend the Ambrosia for dessert, after an interesting, creative meal it was *meh*.
Outstanding food and service! Mixture of subtle tastes are extraordinary. Brandon is the perfect waiter.

Average food at ridiculous prices. In other words, typical DC food scene. Leaving the claw on quail, or chicken legs, or whatever it was that was put in front of me (it is so loud you just nod and make pretend you can hear) may seem cool, but it is just unappealing. Also, when you make a reservation you shouldn't have to wait thirty minutes. Just don't do reservations. The service was slow. The restaurant was packed. It is the current in place to see and be seen, so I guess that is something to consider as you are crammed into a too small table on top of your neighbors and left wondering exactly who it was you came to the restaurant with.
Extraordinary food and extraordinary service.  I would suggest you make a reservation while you still can

Inventive small plates, great for sharing. The desserts are not as inspiring as the rest of the menu, but the variety elsewhere makes up for it. Highly recommend the rabbit and sunchoke pasta on the menu right now.

Had a great meal here. Small restaurant,  intimate setting, great service. Brandon is much more attune than he may appear. He made excellent food and wine recommendations.  Most items on the menu are medium-sized. There are a few small plates,  and just two large plates, of which the duck is one. It was fantastic. Very rich, but the two of us  ate the whole thing after having eaten several other dishes before. The veal breast, uni linguini, and the duck are stand-out dishes.

I really enjoyed my experience here. The food was great, and the flavors well matched. But I wouldn't recommend the buckwheat pancakes with the ice cream and roe. The cold just overpowered the roe and the salt of the roe made worse by the ice cream. Fish and ice cream: do not recommend. But aside from that, everything was delicious, the wait staff friendly and attentive, and the overall atmosphere very comfortable. Portions were on the small side, so prepare to spend a good amount if you need many plates to fill an empty belly.
Experimental tiny plates for those currious and not price sensitive.
Great place, cool ambiance and the bartender Storm is the man!

Bresca is not only the next big thing on 14th. It's a place where you can find the real culinary heaven you're looking for. The complexity of the plates is high, and if you walk through Bresca doors be prepared to start a very intense path into flavours and sensations. It's pretty difficult to find another place like that in DC. It's not super posh, nor pretentious; it's a great opportunity to have a food experience like you never had. So, have faith and follow the chef into this culinary wonderland. It will be a surprise that you will never forget.
Everything taste fresh and new. Definitely worth making the trip and cost!

Fantastic new opening. While you might expect them to over-reach and fail on a couple dishes, everything we had was amazing. The cocktails are definitely unique and the handful of large format beers make for a good change of pace to sharing a bottle of wine.
Delicious food & drinks and very cool vibe!  Definitely try the sea urchin linguine, agnolotti, and cake pops
The space is beautiful, the cocktails are delicious and the food was amazing. Truly a top notch dining experience!

Absolutely wonderful service, food and drinks.. of you are looking for great food for a great price on 14th st, look no more! Chef Ryan and  serving staff Kristen are top of the ladder hands down!!!  Thank you for an amazing dining experience
Just WOW! Prepared to be blown away! Absolutely delicious and beautiful details all around!
Well balanced creative and delicious!
